00:17:15.590 --> 00:17:19.140
It's up to the biologists
how they begin to mine

00:17:19.140 --> 00:17:22.190
this kind of information,
but it is accessible.

00:17:22.190 --> 00:17:24.780
So where do we go from here?

00:17:24.780 --> 00:17:28.320
I think next we'll continue on trying

00:17:28.320 --> 00:17:31.240
to acquire the fly brain atlas.

00:17:31.240 --> 00:17:34.350
That's gonna be a little
bit of a longer-term effort

00:17:34.350 --> 00:17:38.300
and that'll be, then, combined with all

00:17:38.300 --> 00:17:41.420
the neural processing

00:17:41.420 --> 00:17:44.640
to get the synaptic details

00:17:44.640 --> 00:17:47.230
and the connectivity diagram,

00:17:47.230 --> 00:17:50.117
and then that'll be
absorbed by other scientists

00:17:50.117 --> 00:17:53.580
with light imaging and behavior

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:56.270
to really understand the circuitry.

00:17:56.270 --> 00:17:59.330
I think, going on to the
next level beyond that,

00:17:59.330 --> 00:18:02.510
after we have one nice, complete brain,

00:18:02.510 --> 00:18:03.870
you begin to look at differences.

00:18:03.870 --> 00:18:06.940
And I think this will be
another exciting phase

00:18:06.940 --> 00:18:10.070
for this field where we look
at fly-to-fly difference.

